      "preview",
      "withdrawn"
    ],
    "description": "An open-versus-paid boundary, licensing, provenance, or contribution-policy audit row renders at a Stable (or LTS) public claim only when it carries a captured, within-freshness-SLO attestation packet, every required audit control is satisfied, the row owner has signed, any waiver it relies on is unexpired, and the public claim it backs is itself at or above the cutline. A row whose attestation packet breached its freshness SLO or is missing, whose audit control is unsatisfied, whose evidence is incomplete, whose owner sign-off is missing, whose waiver expired, or whose backing public claim is below the cutline narrows to a label below the cutline (beta, preview, withdrawn) and never inherits an adjacent attested row's label."
  },
